This plugin make possible to edit torrent files using vim.

You need vim compiled with python support and hunnyb[1] or bittorent[2]

Its parse the bencode data and presents its in plain text version that can be
edited and saved again to the torrent file.

Install:
To install you can copy the files from the plugin/ dir to your vim runtime.

If you have mkvimball
you can use 
$ make install
to install it.

Usage:
Trackers URL are listed one per line after a 'trackers' line. A trailing
space before the tracker URL is *obligatory*.

Tiers are separated by empty lines or lines containing a single '.' (dot)
character.

Bugs, suggestions and comments can be sent to <kaz.rag@gmail.com>.
[1]: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/HunnyB/
[2]: http://www.bittorrent.com/
[3]: http://mysite.verizon.net/astronaut/src/index.html#MKVIMBALL 
